<div id="review_148404772" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/148404772" />
    <a title="Rick" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1583917-rick"><img alt="Rick" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1600270795p2/1583917.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/148404772?book_show_action=true">Feb 15, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rick" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rick" href="/user/show/1583917-rick">Rick</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781590387269" href="/book/show/625556.So_Great_a_Cause">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer148404772" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13769472174750140835">Gerald Lund put his characters in the various key trek&apos;s for the migration of the Saints including, the pioneer trek from Nauvoo, the Donner Party trek, and the sailing of the Brooklyn ship from New York to yerba buena (San Francisco). The pioneer trek was most interesting as the difficulties faced by the Saints were well portrayed by Lund. In addition, the difficulty Brigham Young must have had with the organization and administration of the entire affair is well penned. The details about the B</span>
  <span id="freeText13769472174750140835" style="display:none">Gerald Lund put his characters in the various key trek's for the migration of the Saints including, the pioneer trek from Nauvoo, the Donner Party trek, and the sailing of the Brooklyn ship from New York to yerba buena (San Francisco). The pioneer trek was most interesting as the difficulties faced by the Saints were well portrayed by Lund. In addition, the difficulty Brigham Young must have had with the organization and administration of the entire affair is well penned. The details about the Brooklyn are interesting. I think many are aware of the voyage but this is the first time I have read any details of where the ship went and what it must have been like. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13769472174750140835" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


