    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2987320972" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2987320972" />
    <a title="Chelsea" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5022240-chelsea"><img alt="Chelsea" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1306434839p2/5022240.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2987320972?book_show_action=true">Jan 31, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chelsea" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chelsea" href="/user/show/5022240-chelsea">Chelsea</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/19860052-so-great-a-cause">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5022240-chelsea?shelf=adult-fiction">adult-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5022240-chelsea?shelf=church">church</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2987320972" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4792408848260123062">Not a lot happens historically with this book. Basically it takes place over four months from February to June 1846 where the saints are just slogging slowly from Nauvoo to the Missouri River. The big focus is on Joshua&apos;s character and how the trek influences him.<br/><br/>Since I read these books more for the historical parts, it was just ok. The fiction part isn&apos;t my favorite in the writing.</span>
  <span id="freeText4792408848260123062" style="display:none">Not a lot happens historically with this book. Basically it takes place over four months from February to June 1846 where the saints are just slogging slowly from Nauvoo to the Missouri River. The big focus is on Joshua's character and how the trek influences him.<br /><br />Since I read these books more for the historical parts, it was just ok. The fiction part isn't my favorite in the writing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4792408848260123062" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


