<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer9824538455208946333">Gerald N. Lund received his B.A. and M.S. degrees in sociology from Brigham Young University. He served for thirty-five years in the Church Educational System, and he served as a member of the Second Quorum of the Seventy from 2002 to 2008. He is a prolific and bestselling author of both fiction and nonfiction and is best known for his historical novels, including <i>The Work and the Glory</i> series, <i>Fi</i></span>
  <span id="freeText9824538455208946333" style="display:none">Gerald N. Lund received his B.A. and M.S. degrees in sociology from Brigham Young University. He served for thirty-five years in the Church Educational System, and he served as a member of the Second Quorum of the Seventy from 2002 to 2008. He is a prolific and bestselling author of both fiction and nonfiction and is best known for his historical novels, including <i>The Work and the Glory</i> series, <i>Fire of the Covenant, The Kingdom and the Crown </i>series, and <i>The Undaunted</i>. He and his late wife, Lynn, are the parents of seven children.<br /></span>
